text: <@U28TLDP0R> White is still good in reanimator strategies. I'm goldfishing a 4-color hatebear reanimator list right now. (no red.) It's a consistent turn 3-4 win when goldfishing albeit no counterspell backup. Feels a lot faster than my old Karador boonweaver list. With that said, I'm running both Boonweaver and Protean Hulk. The alternative is to remove hatebears and add counterspells and go more all-in on the combo, but I'm already so invested in hatebears haha.

I'm kind of sad my deck is getting more streamlined to be honest because I'm having a hard time fitting in my pet cards. Like, hatebears without flying aren't that good. I had to cut Sanctum Prelate because 1WW plus not flying is bad. But Hushwing and Aven Mindcensor fly so they can draw cards off Tymna easier.

now people are thinking about slotting Hulk into Hermit Druid. Two suggestions for instant Hulk wins: Hermit Druid + Mogis's Maurader + Deathrite Shaman for sans-red, and Hermit Druid + Burning-Tree Emissary + Crimson Mage for 5-color.
I think we can just throw out now there are as many ways to do nutty crap with pro-hulk as there are players
